parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag clock spring can prevent the horn from functioning properly, which can lead to accidents due to lack of warning to other drivers. Additionally, it may also prevent the airbag from deploying in the event of an accident, resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The horn does not function
the airbag warning light is illuminated
the airbag may not deploy in the event of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty Takata airbags can deploy unexpectedly, causing injuries or fatalities. The recall process has been slow, leaving vehicles without functioning airbags, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Unexpected airbag deployment
injuries or fatalities due to airbag deployment
inability to get recall repairs in a timely manner.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause accidents, and the failure of airbags to deploy can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Unintended acceleration
airbags do not deploy in the event of an accident
vehicle crashes into other objects.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door lock actuator can trap occupants inside the vehicle, posing a significant safety risk.
symptoms: The door remains locked even when pulling on the interior handle to open the door or when trying to unlock the door using the interior latch
the door does not lock when the vehicle is shifted out of PARK
the audible "beep" is not heard when locking the vehicle using the key fob.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The presence of mold and mildew in the air conditioning system can cause unpleasant odors and potentially lead to health issues.
symptoms: A constant bad moldy/mildew smell coming from the A/C system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling while driving can cause accidents, especially if the vehicle loses power while in motion.
symptoms: The engine shuts off while driving
the vehicle can be restarted but only runs for a short period before dying again.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake pedal design can cause the driver's foot to get caught under the pedal, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brake pedal is too close to the gas pedal
the brake pedal depresses too far
causing the driver to accidentally hit the gas pedal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the outside temperature gauge can cause the driver to be unaware of road conditions, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The outside temperature gauge does not work
is inaccurate
or reacts slowly to changes in temperature.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hatch lift support can cause serious injury or death if the hatch falls on someone.
symptoms: The hatch lift support fails
causing the hatch to fall or not stay up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake pedal sinking or softness can cause a loss of braking power, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sinks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
excessive pressure is required to activate the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hydroboost system can cause a loss of braking power, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sinks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
excessive pressure is required to activate the brakes
the ABS and VSC track lights come on
accompanied by a beeping alarm.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause accidents or near-misses, especially when braking or stopping.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly when braking or stopping
the brake pedal and accelerator pedal are too close
the depressed brake pedal is below the level of the resting accelerator pedal.
